# Cross-compile for raspberry

This is very easy. There is an [article on hackaday](https://hackaday.com/2016/02/03/code-craft-cross-compiling-for-the-raspberry-pi/)
to get you started.

Install the compiler:

	apt install g++-arm-linux-gnueabihf pkg-config-arm-linux-gnueabihf

Download the dependencies:

	# libusb-1.0:
	wget http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/pool/main/libu/libusb-1.0/libusb-1.0-0_1.0.21-1_armhf.deb
	dpkg -x --path-exclude=/usr  libusb-1.0-0_1.0.21-1_armhf.deb .
	ln -s libusb-1.0.so.0.1.0 libusb-1.0.so
	# libudev:
	wget http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/pool/main/s/systemd/libudev1_232-25+deb9u6_armhf.deb
	dpkg -x --path-exclude=/usr  libudev1_232-25+deb9u6_armhf.deb .
